@Html.Partial(MVC.Shared.Views.Title, "icon-like-filled")

<blockquote>
    <p>Don't dress things up, or try to explain them; just write them down, in a list, in the plainest language possible.</p>
    <footer>Nick Hornby, <cite title="High Fidelity">High Fidelity</cite></footer>
</blockquote>
<p>If you've read the book @Bs.Link("High Fidelity", "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/285092.High_Fidelity") then you know that the protagonist, Rob, is obsessed with making lists of things. I can relate. There are a ton of great tools and resources available to software developers and putting stuff in lists helps make sense of it all. To that end, I've curated a few lists of things that I like and will periodically update them as my likes change.</p>
